In article <5082@dartvax.UUCP> vallury@dartvax.UUCP (Vallury Prabhakar) writes:
>Take care not to read more than 1 [scroll of life protection] at a time,
>because irrespective of how many you have read, you get only 1 chance to
>recover.  If you have more than 1 then read one, wait until you have been
>killed, and then if you do manage to survive, read the next one, wait until
>death, ad nauseum.

   This is false.  The effects of life protection are cumulative (so that
if you have read three scrolls, you will be reincarnated three times).
   Why do people post false statements like this??

